SIMPLE: immoderate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immoderate
<hw>Im*mod"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immoderatus</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>moderatus</ets>
moderate. See <er>Moderate</er>.]</ety> <def>Not moderate; exceeding
just or usual and suitable bounds; excessive; extravagant; unreasonable;
<as>as, <ex>immoderate</ex> demands; <ex>immoderate</ex> grief;
<ex>immoderate</ex> laughter.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So every scope by the <qex>immoderate</qex> use⟦br⟧
Turns to restraint.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Excessive; exorbitant; unreasonable; extravagant;
intemperate; inordinate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immoderately</ent>⟦br⟧
